A=U\Sigma V^*
U
V
||U||=||V||=1
\Sigma=diag(\sigma_n,\ldots,\sigma_1)
\sigma_n\geq\cdots\geq\sigma_1\geq0.
\Sigma_p=diag(\sigma_n+1/p,\ldots,\sigma_1+1/p)
A_p=U\Sigma_pV^*\in GL_n(\mathbb{C})
||A-A_p||=||U(\Sigma-\Sigma_p)V^*||\leq||U||||\Sigma-\Sigma_p||||V^*||=||\Sigma-\Sigma_p||=\frac{1}{p}||I_n||,
\lim_{p\to\infty}||A-A_p||=0,
A=U\Sigma V^\ast
A
\Sigma
